===Etymology===
{{etyl|ang}} {{term|ebba|lang=ang}}, from {{proto|Germanic|abjōn}} (compare West Frisian {{term|ebbe|lang=fy}}, Dutch {{term|eb|lang=nl}}, German {{term|Ebbe|lang=de}}, Old Norse {{term|efja|lang=non}} ‘countercurrent’), from {{proto|Germanic|ab|off, away}} (compare Old English {{term|af|lang=ang}}). More at [[of]], [[off]].

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# The receding movement of the [[tide]].
# A gradual decline
# low state, state of depression
# The [[European bunting]]

====Quotations====
